        <h2>Game Overview</h2>
        <p>The 2018 Super Bowl took place on February 4, 2018, at U.S. Bank Stadium in Minneapolis, Minnesota. It was a highly anticipated matchup between the Philadelphia Eagles and the New England Patriots.</p>
        <p>The game was closely contested throughout, with both teams trading scores and momentum. In the end, it came down to the wire, providing one of the most thrilling Super Bowl finishes in history.</p>
        
        <h2>Scoring Plays</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>1st Quarter:</strong> The Eagles scored a touchdown with a pass from Nick Foles to Alshon Jeffery.</li>
            <li><strong>2nd Quarter:</strong> The Patriots responded with a touchdown pass from Tom Brady to Rob Gronkowski.</li>
            <!-- Add more scoring plays -->
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Key Moments</h2>
        <p>Throughout the game, there were several key moments that shifted momentum and kept fans on the edge of their seats:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The Eagles' "Philly Special" trick play, where quarterback Nick Foles caught a touchdown pass.</li>
            <li>The Patriots' comeback attempt in the fourth quarter, led by Tom Brady.</li>
            <!-- Add more key moments -->
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Post-game Reactions</h2>
        <p>After the game, there were mixed emotions from both teams:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Elation from the Philadelphia Eagles, who won their first-ever Super Bowl title.</li>
            <li>Disappointment from the New England Patriots, who fell just short of winning their sixth championship.</li>
